    {
      "id": "0194a1c2c57add9be1cd9f168606f94b78857da5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2013-01-05 16:13:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Verified\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.3/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/87d71efc-5745-11e2-8b17-52540035b04c).  Ran 12 tests.  No failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "2bc775ae6ed55d791ef8495a8529a4986e9eae88",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-08 05:26:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: (1 inline comment)\n\nNot really explained here or in the ticket.\nHow come there's a local lockign failure? We run all locking past the server first, so if the server was able to lock, why would the client not?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "e0c707bdf8c7299fb283ea78e88817aa0ecb2cb4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 188,
        "name": "Andriy Skulysh",
        "email": "andriy.skulysh@seagate.com",
        "username": "askulysh",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-01-08 16:40:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThe error (-ERESTARTSYS) happens on a signal.\nposix_lock_file_wait() can sleep due to unlock race. Previous lock was already unlocked by lustre but not by the kernel.\n\nI prefer to change flock locking oder.\nkernel lock should be taken after lustre lock (current behavior),\nkernel lock should be released prior to lustre lock during unlock.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "df20bc5a407904d34b520249ccf3c39006077cb2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-08 16:47:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nOn one hand I agree that unlocking locally before sending unlock to the server makes sense,\nthough on the other hand what if server refuses to unlock for whatever reason, is this feasible, how can we combat that?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "89efd6b277064e633691972cb8d4f05f42653802",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 188,
        "name": "Andriy Skulysh",
        "email": "andriy.skulysh@seagate.com",
        "username": "askulysh",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-01-08 18:34:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nlocal lock is needed only for releasing locks on exit. It is safe to obtain it in case of failure of unlocking lustre lock.\nThere will not be a conflict because we still hold lustre lock. \n\nBut we can land this patch for now. It fixes an issue without huge changes.",
